  "text": "on a standard beam splitter. This experiment can be thought of a type of quantum eraser (Ref. [CITATION_1] and references therein) where welcher-weg (which-path, or perhaps more accurately \"which non-linearity\") information is erased by the alignment of the signal modes of the two non-linearities in conjunction with the beam splitter which mixes the idler modes. In other words, after the second non-linearity information could in-principle be obtained by seeing which idler mode contained light, but after the beam splitter this information is erased. Then the light field that passes through the sample is discarded. See Figure. 1. This constitutes a type of hybrid interferometer described by neither the SU(2) formalism (standard MZI and variants), nor the SU(1,1) formalism (Yurke-Type interferometers).",
